# How It Works

SafeScan monitors runtime application activity through Android system APIs and background services. The application analyzes behavioral patterns such as application usage activity, network statistics, and package information to identify potentially suspicious behavior.

Detected events are logged locally and synchronized with cloud storage using Firebase services. Users receive real-time alerts and can review detected risks directly within the application interface.

